                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>A third meeting in 1954 of the <gloss target="#t_ANZUS1">ANZUS</gloss> Council
                    Deputies was held in Washington on the afternoon of August 5. Under Secretary
                    Smith led the United States participants; Ambassadors Spender and Munro led the
                    Australian and New Zealand participants. Procedural questions relating to the
                    formation of <gloss target="#t_SEATO1">SEATO</gloss> occupied most of the
                    discussion. United States minutes of the meeting, drafted by Foster, are in
                    Conference files, lot 60 D 627, <gloss target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 355.</p>
            </div>
